Uses contextual understanding.

Models:

BERT
RoBERTa
GPT embeddings
MiniLM

These understand:

context
grammar
semantics
ambiguity

Example:

“Apple released a phone”
“Apple pie tastes good”

Transformer embeddings distinguish company vs fruit.

6. Character-Based Similarity

Useful for noisy or short text.

N-grams / Shingling

Break text into chunks.

Example bigrams for “hello”:

he
el
ll
lo

Then compare overlap.

Useful for:

plagiarism detection
typo tolerance
language detection
7. Phonetic Similarity

Compares pronunciation.

Algorithms:

Soundex
Metaphone
Double Metaphone

Useful for:

name matching
speech systems

Example:

“Smith”
“Smyth”
8. Sequence Alignment Techniques

Borrowed from bioinformatics.

Algorithms:

Needleman-Wunsch
Smith-Waterman

Useful for:

DNA-like sequence comparison
advanced fuzzy matching
9. Hybrid / AI Retrieval Methods

Modern search systems combine techniques.

Typical pipeline:

BM25 keyword retrieval
Embedding similarity
Reranking with transformers

Used in:

semantic search
RAG systems
vector databases
